<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 98-03-03 - 2-Stage Steer Axle Springs with Shock Absorbers</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi980303" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>98-03-03</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>December, 1998</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>SPRINGS</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>2-Stage Steer Axle Springs with Shock Absorbers</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>5000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>02/01/1994</startdate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to 5000 SFA models built after January, 1994.</para>
                <para>Special mixer applications of the 5000 SFA model equipped with aft mounted, hydraulic applied,
                    axles to provide steer axle loading to meet bridge formulae result in very light steer axle loading
                    when empty with the boost axle in the up position. Under these conditions, the steer axle loading is
                    significantly below the 20K nominal spring capacity, which may result in a harsh ride. This
                    condition is accentuated on concrete road surfaces with divider strips; and is dependent on vehicle
                    speed and divider strip spacing.
                </para>
                <para>To improve ride comfort, 2-stage steer axle springs and shock absorbers are available for
                    retrofitting the vehicle. The first stage of the 2-stage spring is designed to match typical
                    unloaded condition with this type vehicle and the shock absorbers enhance ride quality.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
